org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.statistics.binning

Class NumericRangeFieldValueBinningStrategy

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.statistics.binning.FieldValueBinningStrategy
      • org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.statistics.binning.NumericRangeFieldValueBinningStrategy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Persistable, BinningStrategy, StatisticBinningStrategy

    public class NumericRangeFieldValueBinningStrategy
extends FieldValueBinningStrategy
    Statistic binning strategy that bins statistic values by the numeric representation of the value of a given field. By default it will truncate decimal places and will bin by the integer. However, an "offset" and "interval" can be provided to bin numbers at any regular step-sized increment from an origin value. A statistic using this binning strategy can be constrained using numeric ranges (Apache-Commons `Range` class can be used as a constraint).
